app.comment: A library to create tower defense games. See main for example.

xq8xGLTujvcBaFGI46ICP5Iw.text: This library maintains a set of towers defending against attackers. The towers do not move while the attacker may have any trajectory.

x2dtWdIGw4uJ8wHx9snttXN6.text: The library works with a board so it needs to be initialized once with the board you are using in your game (a landscape board in this case).

Uzdqpqs84vIj6zDIDNOoNWN4.text: Make sure to call 'initialize' once with the game board.

G0LeX3Foviy0nHc0Mwa4n1zL.text: You can create any kind of sprite (ellipse, rectangle, picture,...) and register it as a 'tower'. You can add as many towers as you wish.

Kod6gxxkVaL5ZPxj7j9BJilE.text: Remember, towers are not supposed to move.

DRpefq0ta79B3myIl2jfpZV3.text: When adding a tower, you specify also its characteristics:

g01MCDi261hmvpRUOCn3Jkqg.text: * the power of the bullets (35 here)

G0LeX3Foviy0nHc0Mwa4n1zL.text: You can add any kind of sprite (ellipse, rectangle, picture,...) as a 'tower'. When adding a tower, you specify also its characteristics:

TWUHejXyKAqMYQBP8Ux840b7.text: You can also add any kind of sprite as an 'attacker'. When you add the attacker, you also specify its life (65 here).

BIXibfW2eHYkEfm2DXr1Tjyg.text: Attackers can freely move on the board.
